    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The stored procedure "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "USP_RetrieveAvailableBudgetGroups",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " is designed to retrieve a list of active budget groups from a view named "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "BudgetApp_vwBudgetGroups",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " within the "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "EC3DB",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " database. It selects specific columns related to budget groups, including an energy unit that is determined based on the type of energy associated with each budget group. The procedure also adds metadata such as the current date and a default user for creation and modification details."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The procedure is straightforward, involving a single "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "SELECT",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " statement with a "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "CASE",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " expression to determine the energy unit. It does not involve any complex logic, joins, or subqueries, making it relatively simple."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "This stored procedure does not take any input parameters. It operates on the assumption that it will always retrieve all active budget groups from the specified view."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "4. Business Logic and Workflow"
        }
      ]
